3GPP TS 29.510 V17.16.0; 5G System; Network Function Repository Services; Stage 3

NF Instances (Store)

Search a collection of NF Instances

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
query Parameters
required
string or string (NFType)

Type of the target NF

required
string or string (NFType)

Type of the requester NF

Array of strings or strings (CollocatedNfType) non-empty

collocated NF types that candidate NFs should preferentially support

requester-nf-instance-id
string <uuid> (NfInstanceId)

NfInstanceId of the requester NF

Array of strings or strings (ServiceName) non-empty unique

Names of the services offered by the NF

requester-nf-instance-fqdn
string (Fqdn) [ 4 .. 253 ] characters ^([0-9A-Za-z]([-0-9A-Za-z]{0,61}[0-9A-Za-z])?...

FQDN of the requester NF

Array of objects (PlmnId) non-empty

Id of the PLMN of either the target NF, or in SNPN scenario the Credentials Holder in the PLMN

Array of objects (PlmnId) non-empty

Id of the PLMN where the NF issuing the Discovery request is located

target-nf-instance-id
string <uuid> (NfInstanceId)

Identity of the NF instance being discovered

target-nf-fqdn
string (Fqdn) [ 4 .. 253 ] characters ^([0-9A-Za-z]([-0-9A-Za-z]{0,61}[0-9A-Za-z])?...

FQDN of the NF instance being discovered

hnrf-uri
string (Uri)

Uri of the home NRF

Array of objects (Snssai) non-empty

Slice info of the target NF

Array of objects (ExtSnssai) non-empty

Slice info of the requester NF

Array of objects (PlmnSnssai) non-empty

PLMN specific Slice info of the target NF

Array of objects (PlmnSnssai) non-empty

PLMN-specific slice info of the NF issuing the Discovery request

dnn
string (Dnn)

Dnn supported by the BSF, SMF or UPF

integer or string (IpIndex)

The IPv4 Index supported by the candidate UPF.

integer or string (IpIndex)

The IPv6 Index supported by the candidate UPF.

nsi-list
Array of strings non-empty

NSI IDs that are served by the services being discovered

string
mbsmf-serving-area

object (Tai)

string (AmfRegionId) ^[A-Fa-f0-9]{2}$

object (Guami)

Guami used to search for an appropriate AMF

supi
string (Supi) ^(imsi-[0-9]{5,15}|nai-.+|gci-.+|gli-.+|.+)$

SUPI of the user

ue-ipv4-address
string (Ipv4Addr) ^(([0-9]|[1-9][0-9]|1[0-9][0-9]|2[0-4][0-9]|2...
Example: ue-ipv4-address=198.51.100.1

IPv4 address of the UE

ip-domain
string

IP domain of the UE, which supported by BSF

ue-ipv6-prefix
string (Ipv6Prefix) ^((([^:]+:){7}([^:]+))|((([^:]+:)*[^:]+)?::((...
Example: ue-ipv6-prefix=2001:db8:abcd:12::0/64

IPv6 prefix of the UE

pgw-ind
boolean

Combined PGW-C and SMF or a standalone SMF

preferred-pgw-ind
boolean

Indicates combined PGW-C+SMF or standalone SMF are preferred

pgw
string (Fqdn) [ 4 .. 253 ] characters ^([0-9A-Za-z]([-0-9A-Za-z]{0,61}[0-9A-Za-z])?...

PGW FQDN of a combined PGW-C and SMF

object or object or object (IpAddr)

PGW IP Address of a combined PGW-C and SMF

string (ExtGroupId) ^extgroupid-[^@]+@[^@]+$

boolean
